## 1. Project Overview

UniTrack is a **real-time university bus tracking system** that allows students and faculty of Ganpat University to track campus buses live on a map. Drivers use the app to broadcast their GPS location, and students/faculty see those buses moving in real-time on an interactive map.

### Problem Statement
Students and faculty often wait long periods at bus stops without knowing when their bus will arrive, leading to missed buses and wasted time.

### Solution
A web + mobile application with:
- **Live GPS tracking** of university buses on an interactive map
- **Role-based dashboards** for Admin, Driver, Student, and Faculty
- **Real-time updates** powered by Firebase Realtime Database
- **Offline support** with queued GPS updates
- **PWA + Native Android** deployment via Capacitor

### User Roles

| Role | Access | Key Features |
|------|--------|--------------|
| **Admin** | Full system control | Manage buses, routes, drivers, schedules, users, analytics |
| **Driver** | Driver dashboard | Check-in/out, GPS broadcasting, route navigation, break mode |
| **Student** | Tracking map | View live buses, filter by route, favorite routes |
| **Faculty** | Tracking map | Same as student (shared tracking view) |

