### High-Level Architecture Diagram

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Client Side"
        A[React + Vite SPA]
        B[Android App via Capacitor]
    end

    subgraph "Firebase Cloud"
        C[Firebase Authentication]
        D[Cloud Firestore]
        E[Realtime Database]
        F[Firebase Hosting]
    end

    subgraph "External APIs"
        G[OpenStreetMap Tiles]
        H[Nominatim Geocoding]
    end

    A --> C
    B --> C
    A --> D
    B --> D
    A --> E
    B --> E
    F --> A
    A --> G
    A --> H
```

### Architecture Pattern: **Serverless / BaaS (Backend-as-a-Service)**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This project uses a **fully serverless architecture** — there is NO custom backend server (no Express, no Node.js server). All backend logic is handled by Firebase services directly from the client. This is a key architectural decision to discuss in your presentation.

### Why Serverless?
1. **Zero server management** — Firebase handles scaling, uptime, and infrastructure
2. **Real-time out of the box** — Firebase RTDB provides WebSocket-based real-time sync
3. **Built-in authentication** — No need to implement JWT, session management, etc.
4. **Security rules** — Server-side validation without writing server code
5. **Free tier sufficient** — Firebase's free (Spark) plan covers a university-scale project

