### 4.3 Code Splitting & Lazy Loading

All major page components are **lazy loaded** using React's `lazy()` and `Suspense`:

```javascript
const LandingPage = lazy(() => import('@/pages/LandingPage'));
const LoginPage = lazy(() => import('@/pages/LoginPage'));
const AdminDashboard = lazy(() => import('@/pages/admin/AdminDashboard'));
const DriverView = lazy(() => import('@/pages/driver/DriverView'));
const TrackingPage = lazy(() => import('@/pages/track'));
```

**Benefits:**
- Reduces initial bundle size
- Users only download code for pages they visit
- Faster Time to First Paint (TTFP)

