## 8. Authentication & Authorization

### 8.1 Authentication Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant App as React App
    participant Auth as Firebase Auth
    participant FS as Firestore

    U->>App: Enter email + password
    App->>Auth: signInWithEmailAndPassword()
    Auth-->>App: Firebase User object (uid, email)
    App->>FS: getDoc('users/{uid}')
    FS-->>App: User profile (role, name, etc.)
    App->>App: Set AuthContext (user + role)
    App->>App: Navigate to role-based dashboard
```

### 8.2 Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

**Client-side:** `ProtectedRoute` component wraps each route:

```jsx
<Route path="/admin/*" element={
    <ProtectedRoute allowedRoles={['admin']}>
        <AdminDashboard />
    </ProtectedRoute>
} />
```

**Server-side:** Firestore Security Rules enforce access:

```
// Only admin can write to buses, routes, shifts, schedules
match /buses/{busId} {
    allow read: if isAuthenticated();
    allow write: if isAdmin();
}

// Drivers can only write their own trip history
match /tripHistory/{tripId} {
    allow create: if isAuthenticated() && hasRole('driver');
}
```

### 8.3 RTDB Security Rules

```json
{
  "busLocations": {
    ".read": "auth != null",
    "$driverId": {
      ".write": "auth != null && auth.uid == $driverId"
    }
  },
  "driverStatus": {
    ".read": "auth != null",
    "$driverId": {
      ".write": "auth != null && auth.uid == $driverId"
    }
  }
}
```

**Key Security Principle:** Drivers can only write to their own location node (`auth.uid == $driverId`), but all authenticated users can read all bus locations.

