## 9. Real-Time GPS Tracking System

### 9.1 Architecture — How Live Tracking Works

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Driver as Driver App
    participant GPS as Device GPS
    participant RTDB as Firebase RTDB
    participant Student as Student App
    participant Map as Leaflet Map

    Driver->>GPS: watchPosition() (continuous)
    GPS-->>Driver: Position {lat, lng, speed, heading, accuracy}
    Driver->>RTDB: set('busLocations/{driverId}', locationData)
    RTDB-->>Student: onValue('busLocations') → real-time push
    Student->>Map: Update bus marker position
    Map-->>Student: Animated marker movement
```

### 9.2 Driver-Side: GPS Broadcasting

The [useDriverTracking](file:///c:/metallic-oort/client/src/pages/driver/hooks/useDriverTracking.js) hook manages:

1. **GPS Watch** — `navigator.geolocation.watchPosition()` with high accuracy
2. **Firebase Write** — Writes to `busLocations/{driverId}` on each position update
3. **Offline Queue** — When offline, GPS updates are queued in `localStorage` and flushed when back online
4. **Pause Mode** — Driver can pause tracking (e.g., at a stop) — GPS continues but Firebase writes `isPaused: true`
5. **Ref-based Callbacks** — Uses React refs to avoid stale closures in the GPS callback

**Location Update Payload:**
```javascript
{
    lat: 23.529,
    lng: 72.457,
    heading: 180,        // Compass direction (degrees)
    speed: 12.5,         // m/s
    accuracy: 8.3,       // meters
    driverId: "user-id",
    routeId: "route-id",
    routeName: "Route Name",
    isActive: true,
    isPaused: false,
    lastUpdated: 1703169600000  // Unix timestamp
}
```

### 9.3 Student-Side: Real-Time Listening

The [useBusLocations](file:///c:/metallic-oort/client/src/pages/track/hooks/useBusLocations.js) hook:

1. Subscribes to `busLocations` node via `onValue()` (WebSocket)
2. Filters for `isActive: true` buses only
3. Monitors connection status via `.info/connected`
4. Provides a `refresh()` function for manual reconnection

### 9.4 Offline Support

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[GPS Position Update] --> B{Is Online?}
    B -->|Yes| C{Is Paused?}
    C -->|No| D[Write to Firebase RTDB]
    C -->|Yes| E[Skip write, update isPaused flag]
    B -->|No| F[Queue in localStorage]
    F --> G[Monitor online/offline events]
    G -->|Back Online| H[Flush queue to Firebase]
```

### 9.5 ETA Calculation

The [eta.js](file:///c:/metallic-oort/client/src/pages/driver/utils/eta.js) utility uses the **Haversine formula** for great-circle distance:

```javascript
// Haversine formula for distance between two GPS coordinates
const R = 6371e3; // Earth radius in meters
const a = sin²(Δlat/2) + cos(lat1) × cos(lat2) × sin²(Δlng/2);
const distance = R × 2 × atan2(√a, √(1-a));

// ETA = distance / speed
const eta = distance / (speed || defaultSpeed);
```

