## 10. Mobile App (Capacitor)

### 10.1 What is Capacitor?

Capacitor is an open-source native runtime by Ionic that wraps web apps into native mobile shells (like a WebView), providing access to native device APIs (GPS, camera, etc.) through JavaScript plugins.

### 10.2 Configuration

```json
// capacitor.config.json
{
    "appId": "com.unitrack.app",
    "appName": "UniTrack",
    "webDir": "dist",
    "server": {
        "androidScheme": "https"
    },
    "android": {
        "allowMixedContent": false,
        "backgroundColor": "#0f0f1a"
    }
}
```

### 10.3 Build Process

```
1. npm run build          → Builds React app to client/dist/
2. npx cap sync android   → Copies dist/ to Android project
3. npx cap open android   → Opens in Android Studio
4. Build APK              → Gradle builds the .apk
```

### 10.4 Native Plugin: Geolocation

```javascript
import { Geolocation } from '@capacitor/geolocation';

// Request permissions (Android)
await Geolocation.requestPermissions();

// Watch position (uses native GPS)
const watchId = await Geolocation.watchPosition({
    enableHighAccuracy: true
}, (position) => {
    // Update location in Firebase
});
```

