## 12. Security

### 12.1 Security Layers

| Layer | Mechanism | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| **Client Routing** | `ProtectedRoute` component | Prevents UI access by role |
| **Firestore Rules** | Server-side rules file | Prevents unauthorized data read/write |
| **RTDB Rules** | `database.rules.json` | Prevents GPS location spoofing |
| **Firebase Auth** | Firebase-managed sessions | Handles token refresh, expiry |
| **HTTPS** | Enforced by Firebase Hosting | Encrypted data in transit |
| **Environment Variables** | `.env` file (not committed) | Protects API keys from source code |

### 12.2 Firestore Security Rules — Key Patterns

```javascript
// Helper: Check if user is authenticated
function isAuthenticated() {
    return request.auth != null;
}

// Helper: Check user role from Firestore
function hasRole(role) {
    return isAuthenticated() && 
           get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.role == role;
}

// Helper: Check if admin
function isAdmin() {
    return hasRole('admin');
}
```

### 12.3 Data Validation

| Validation | Where | How |
|-----------|-------|-----|
| Email format | Client (`userCreation.js`) | Regex + domain check |
| Duplicate email | Client + Firestore query | `checkEmailExists()` |
| Required fields | Client (`validateUserData()`) | Array of error messages |
| Role validation | Client + Security Rules | Whitelist check |
| Birthday format | Client (`birthdayToPassword()`) | Date parsing |

---

## 13. Design Patterns & Architectural Decisions

### 13.1 Patterns Used

| Pattern | Where | Purpose |
|---------|-------|---------|
| **Service Layer** | `services/*.js` | Abstracts Firebase SDK calls behind clean APIs |
| **Custom Hooks** | `hooks/*.js` | Encapsulates data fetching + state management |
| **Context Provider** | `AuthContext.jsx` | Global auth state without prop drilling |
| **Lazy Loading** | `App.jsx` | Code splitting per route |
| **Barrel Exports** | `index.js` files | Clean imports from component directories |
| **Secondary App** | `firebase.js` | Prevents admin logout during user creation |
| **Offline Queue** | `useDriverTracking.js` | GPS resilience via `localStorage` |
| **Debounce** | `geocoding.js` | Rate-limits API calls during typing |
| **Ref-based Callbacks** | `useDriverTracking.js` | Prevents stale closures in GPS watch |
| **Builder Pattern** | `RouteBuilder.jsx` | Visual route construction with drag-and-drop stops |
| **Service Worker Caching** | `vite.config.js` | Offline map tiles + asset caching |
| **Glassmorphism Design** | `index.css` | Modern frosted-glass UI aesthetic |

### 13.2 Key Architectural Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| **Firebase (not custom server)** | Eliminates server management, provides real-time sync out of box |
| **RTDB for GPS (not Firestore)** | Lower latency for high-frequency writes (GPS updates every 3s) |
| **Firestore for everything else** | Better querying, document model, offline persistence |
| **Capacitor (not React Native)** | Reuses web codebase entirely — one codebase for web + Android |
| **Leaflet (not Google Maps)** | Free, open-source, no API key needed |
| **CSS variables (not Tailwind)** | Full design system control, smaller bundle |
| **Vanilla CSS (component-scoped)** | Each component has its own `.css` file — no conflicts |
| **Email/Password auth (not OAuth)** | University-controlled accounts with predictable email formats |

