## 19. Android App — Deep Dive

### 19.1 Android Manifest Permissions

From [AndroidManifest.xml](file:///c:/metallic-oort/client/android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml):

```xml
<!-- Required Permissions -->
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION" />
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION" />
<uses-feature android:name="android.hardware.location.gps" />
```

| Permission | Type | Purpose |
|-----------|------|---------|
| `INTERNET` | Normal (auto-granted) | Firebase connection, map tiles, API calls |
| `ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION` | Dangerous (requires user consent) | Cell tower/Wi-Fi based approximate location |
| `ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION` | Dangerous (requires user consent) | GPS-based precise location (critical for tracking) |
| `android.hardware.location.gps` | Hardware feature | Declares GPS is **required** — Google Play won't show app on devices without GPS |

### 19.2 Android Activity Configuration

```xml
<activity
    android:configChanges="orientation|keyboardHidden|keyboard|screenSize|locale|
                           smallestScreenSize|screenLayout|uiMode"
    android:name=".MainActivity"
    android:launchMode="singleTask"
    android:exported="true">
```

| Property | Value | Purpose |
|----------|-------|---------|
| `configChanges` | Multiple | Prevents activity restart on rotation/keyboard changes (WebView handles it) |
| `launchMode` | `singleTask` | Only one instance of the app exists (deep links reuse it) |
| `exported` | `true` | Activity can be launched from outside (required for LAUNCHER) |

### 19.3 Android Dependencies

| Library | Version | Purpose |
|---------|---------|---------|
| `androidx.appcompat` | 1.6.1 | Backward-compatible Android UI |
| `androidx.coordinatorlayout` | 1.2.0 | Layout coordination |
| `androidx.core:core-splashscreen` | 1.0.1 | Native splash screen |
| `androidx.webkit` | 1.9.0 | Modern WebView features |
| `capacitor-android` | (project) | Capacitor runtime |
| Google GMS (optional) | 4.4.0 | Google services (push notifications) |

