## 21. Haptic Feedback System

The app implements a comprehensive **haptic feedback system** using the [Vibration API](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Vibration_API) for mobile devices. See [haptics.js](file:///c:/metallic-oort/client/src/pages/driver/utils/haptics.js).

### 21.1 Haptic Patterns

| Pattern | Vibration (ms) | Trigger |
|---------|---------------|---------|
| `hapticLight` | `[10]` | Light UI interaction |
| `hapticMedium` | `[25]` | Button press |
| `hapticHeavy` | `[50]` | Strong confirmation |
| `hapticSuccess` | `[20, 50, 20]` | Successful action (two bursts) |
| `hapticError` | `[100]` | Error occurred (long buzz) |
| `hapticNotification` | `[30, 100, 30]` | System notification |
| `hapticDoublePulse` | `[30, 80, 30]` | Going online confirmation |
| `hapticCelebration` | `[50, 100, 50, 100, 100]` | Route completed |
| `hapticArrival` | `[40, 60, 20]` | Arrived at a stop |
| `hapticWarning` | `[80, 50, 80]` | Important alert |
| `hapticSelection` | `[5]` | Subtle selection feedback |

### 21.2 Safety Check

```javascript
const isVibrationSupported = typeof navigator !== 'undefined' && 'vibrate' in navigator;
```

The system checks for Vibration API support before every call — silently does nothing on unsupported devices (desktop browsers, older iOS).

---

## 22. Error Handling System

### 22.1 Firebase Auth Error Translation

The login page translates Firebase error codes to **user-friendly messages**:

| Firebase Error Code | User Message |
|--------------------|--------------|
| `auth/user-not-found` | "No account found with this email" |
| `auth/wrong-password` | "Incorrect password" |
| `auth/invalid-email` | "Invalid email address" |
| `auth/too-many-requests` | "Too many attempts. Try again later" |
| `auth/invalid-credential` | "Invalid email or password" |
| Default | "Something went wrong. Please try again." |

### 22.2 Geolocation Error Handling

The [useUserLocation](file:///c:/metallic-oort/client/src/pages/track/hooks/useUserLocation.js) hook handles platform-aware errors:

| Error Type | Android Message | Web Message |
|-----------|----------------|-------------|
| **GPS Disabled** | "Turn on Location/GPS in your device..." | Same |
| **Permission Denied** | "Go to Settings > App > UniTrack > Permissions..." | "Enable location in your browser settings" |
| **Location Unavailable** | "Turn on GPS in device Settings > Location" | Same |
| **Timeout** | "Location request timed out" | Same |
| **Unknown** | "Failed to get location" | Same |

### 22.3 Platform Detection

```javascript
import { Capacitor } from '@capacitor/core';

if (Capacitor.isNativePlatform()) {
    // Android-specific behavior
    await Geolocation.requestPermissions();
} else {
    // Browser-specific behavior
    navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(...);
}
```

The app detects whether it's running in a native Capacitor shell or a browser, and adjusts permission flows and error messages accordingly.

