## 23. AuthContext — Deep Dive

The [AuthContext](file:///c:/metallic-oort/client/src/contexts/AuthContext.jsx) is the heart of state management:

### 23.1 Context Value (what every component can access)

```javascript
const value = {
    user,              // Full user object (uid, email, name, role, phone, etc.)
    userRole,          // 'admin' | 'driver' | 'student' | 'faculty'
    loading,           // True while auth is initializing
    error,             // Auth error messages
    signIn,            // function(email, password): Logs in
    signOut,           // function(): Logs out
    isAuthenticated,   // boolean: is user logged in?
    isAdmin,           // boolean: userRole === 'admin'
    isDriver,          // boolean: userRole === 'driver'
    isStudent          // boolean: userRole === 'student' || 'faculty'
};
```

### 23.2 Auth Flow — Detailed

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[App Starts] --> B["onAuthStateChanged() fires"]
    B --> C{Firebase User exists?}
    C -->|No| D["setUser(null), setLoading(false)"]
    D --> E[Show Landing/Login Page]
    C -->|Yes| F["getDoc('users/{uid}')"]
    F --> G{Firestore doc exists?}
    G -->|Yes| H["Set user + role, setLoading(false)"]
    H --> I[Redirect to role dashboard]
    G -->|No| J["Set user without role"]
    J --> K[Limbo state - shouldn't happen normally]
```

