## 24. Bulk Import System — Deep Dive

### 24.1 Excel/CSV Parsing

The [excelParser.js](file:///c:/metallic-oort/client/src/services/excelParser.js) service:

1. Accepts `.xlsx`, `.xls`, or `.csv` files
2. Uses **SheetJS (XLSX)** library to parse binary Excel data
3. Normalizes column headers (handles case insensitivity, alternate names)
4. Returns structured array of user objects

### 24.2 Column Mapping

| Expected Column | Alt Names Accepted | Required? |
|----------------|-------------------|-----------|
| `name` | `fullname`, `full name`, `student name` | ✅ Yes |
| `rollNo` | `roll_no`, `roll number`, `enrollment` | ✅ Yes (students) |
| `role` | `type`, `user type` | ✅ Yes |
| `phone` | `mobile`, `contact`, `phone number` | ❌ Optional |
| `birthday` | `dob`, `date of birth`, `birthdate` | ✅ Yes (used for password) |
| `email` | `email address` | ✅ Yes (drivers only) |

### 24.3 Bulk Creation Process

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["Upload .xlsx file"] --> B["Parse with SheetJS"]
    B --> C["Normalize columns"]
    C --> D["validateBulkData()"]
    D --> E["Check duplicates within file"]
    E --> F["Show preview table"]
    F --> G{User clicks Import?}
    G -->|Yes| H["bulkCreateUsers() loop"]
    H --> I["For each user:"]
    I --> J["1. validateUserData()"]
    J --> K["2. createSingleUser() via Secondary Auth"]
    K --> L["3. setDoc() Firestore profile"]
    L --> M["4. Progress callback → UI update"]
    M --> N{More users?}
    N -->|Yes| I
    N -->|No| O["Show success/failure report"]
    O --> P["generateErrorReport() → CSV download"]
```

### 24.4 Rate Limiting Protection

```javascript
// 100ms delay between each user creation to prevent Firebase rate limiting
if (i < users.length - 1) {
    await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 100));
}
```

### 24.5 Password Generation Logic

```
For Students/Faculty:
  Email = rollNo@gnu.ac.in  (e.g., 22BIT086@gnu.ac.in)
  Password = birthday in DDMMYYYY format (e.g., 15062003)

For Drivers:
  Email = provided email
  Password = birthday in DDMMYYYY format
```

