## 25. Schedule Template System

### 25.1 How Templates Work

Templates allow admins to define recurring schedules and **bulk-generate** them:

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["Create Template"] --> B["Define: Driver + Bus + Route + Shift"]
    B --> C["Select Days of Week"]
    C --> D["Admin selects date range"]
    D --> E["generateDates() → array of dates"]
    E --> F["generateScheduleEntries() → schedule docs"]
    F --> G["Batch write to Firestore"]
```

### 25.2 Template Data Model

```javascript
{
    name: "Morning Ahmedabad Route",
    driverId: "<driver-uid>",
    busId: "<bus-doc-id>",
    routeId: "<route-doc-id>",
    shiftId: "<shift-doc-id>",
    daysOfWeek: ["monday", "tuesday", "wednesday", "thursday", "friday"],
    isActive: true,
    createdAt: serverTimestamp()
}
```

### 25.3 Date Generation Algorithm

```javascript
function generateDates(daysOfWeek, startDate, endDate) {
    const dates = [];
    const current = new Date(startDate);
    const dayNames = ['sunday', 'monday', ...]; // 0-indexed

    while (current <= endDate) {
        if (daysOfWeek.includes(dayNames[current.getDay()])) {
            dates.push(formatDate(current)); // "YYYY-MM-DD"
        }
        current.setDate(current.getDate() + 1);
    }
    return dates;
}
```

**Example:** Template with `["monday", "wednesday", "friday"]` for Jan 1–Jan 31 generates ~13 schedule entries.

