## 27. Comparison with Existing Solutions

### 27.1 UniTrack vs Other Bus Tracking Apps

| Feature | UniTrack | Google Maps Transit | Moovit | College Bus Apps (generic) |
|---------|----------|-------------------|--------|---------------------------|
| **University-specific** | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| **Custom routes** | ✅ Admin creates routes | ❌ Uses public transit data | ❌ | ⚠️ Usually hardcoded |
| **Real-time GPS** | ✅ Live driver GPS | ✅ For public buses only | ✅ | ⚠️ Often delayed |
| **Admin dashboard** | ✅ Full CRUD | ❌ | ❌ | ⚠️ Basic |
| **Bulk user import** | ✅ Excel/CSV | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ |
| **Offline support** | ✅ GPS queuing | ✅ Cached routes | ⚠️ | ❌ Usually |
| **Cross-platform** | ✅ Web + Android | ✅ Web + Mobile | ✅ | ⚠️ Usually one platform |
| **Cost** | Free (Firebase Spark) | Free | Free | Varies |
| **Schedule management** | ✅ Templates + Calendar | ❌ | ❌ | ⚠️ Basic |
| **Driver management** | ✅ Full driver profiles | ❌ | ❌ | ⚠️ |
| **Open-source maps** | ✅ OpenStreetMap | ❌ Google Maps (paid for API) | ❌ | Varies |

### 27.2 Why Not Just Use Google Maps?

1. **No driver management** — Google Maps has no concept of "drivers" or "admin panels"
2. **No custom routes** — Only supports public transit routes
3. **API costs** — Google Maps Platform charges $7/1000 map loads; OSM is free
4. **No university context** — Can't assign buses to shifts or manage schedules
5. **No offline GPS queuing** — No custom tracking logic possible

---

## 28. Limitations & Known Constraints

### 28.1 Current Limitations

| Limitation | Reason | Possible Future Solution |
|-----------|--------|------------------------|
| **Android only** (no iOS APK) | iOS requires Apple Developer account ($99/year) + Mac for build | Add iOS platform via Capacitor |
| **No push notifications** | Firebase Cloud Messaging not integrated yet | Add FCM for bus arrival alerts |
| **No route turn-by-turn** | Leaflet doesn't have built-in routing engine | Integrate OSRM or Mapbox Directions |
| **GPS accuracy varies** | Depends on device hardware, urban canyons, weather | Implement Kalman filter for smoothing |
| **No multi-language** | Only English UI | Add i18n with `react-intl` or `i18next` |
| **No dark/light toggle** | Dark theme only | Add theme switching in settings |
| **No bus capacity display** | No sensor for passenger count | Integrate IoT passenger counter |
| **Straight-line ETA** | Haversine gives air distance, not road distance | Use OSRM for road-based ETA |
| **No payment/ticketing** | Out of scope | Integrate Razorpay or UPI |
| **Single university** | Hardcoded for GNU | Make university configurable |

### 28.2 Scalability Considerations

| Factor | Current Capacity | At Scale |
|--------|-----------------|----------|
| **Firebase Spark (Free)** | 50K reads/day, 20K writes/day | Upgrade to Blaze (pay-as-you-go) |
| **Simultaneous RTDB connections** | 200 concurrent | Firebase auto-scales up to 200K |
| **Map tiles** | Shared OSM server | Self-host tile server or use Mapbox |
| **Drivers broadcasting** | Tested with ~5 concurrent | Should handle 50+ without issues |
| **Firestore document size** | 1 MB max per document | Route stops kept under limit |

